"manpage for the ALX simple shell project."
.TH hsh 1 "December 8th" "1.0" "hsh - Simple_Shell General Commands Manual"
.SH NAME
hsh Simple Shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.I [OPTIONS] [FILE]
.B Interactive mode
.I [command_name][option_name][argument ...]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The simple shell is a program that takes commands from the keyboard and gives them to the operating system to perform. The simple shell reads input in terms of lines from a file and breaks it up into words at whitespaces. 
.SH EXAMPLES
$ ./hsh
 simple@shell $ ls
 README.md exec.c main.h main.c prompt.c
 simple@shell $
 simple@shell $ exit
 $
.PP
 $ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
 README.md exec.c holberton.h main.c prompt.c
 $

 .SH INSTALLATION
.I To install:
.br

.B git clone https://github.com/Ochiengmorris/simple_shell.git
br

.I Compile files using:
.br

.B gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic *.c -o hsh
.br
.br
.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1)
